[3] Cholera - Pakistan: (Zhob, Balochistan)
Date: Sat 16 Jul 2022
Source: Pakistan Today [edited]
https://www.pakistantoday.com.pk/2022/07/16/13-die-as-cholera-on-rise-in-zhob/


As many as 13 people have died of cholera in Zhob including 9 patients who died in District Headquarters Hospital, the health authorities have informed.

According to district officer health (DO-H) Zhob Dr Muzaffar Shah, deaths from cholera have also been reported in the area outside the District Headquarters Hospital. "So far from 5 Jul 2022, 2334 patients of cholera have been reported in the District Headquarters Hospital Zhob," the district officer pointed out, adding that 462 patients were brought to the hospital on Sat, 16 Jul 2022, alone.

According to reports, cholera has afflicted hundreds of people in Zhob district in the past week. "Women and children are among the worst hit by the water-borne disease," the DHO said. An emergency has been declared in the district to cope with increasing cases of cholera disease. The main reason behind the outbreak of cholera is the use of contaminated water by the people.

